Course gives general overview of the early modern history of Russia in the 18th century. Treated are the main topics like social, economic, ecclesiastic history etc. Special attention is turned to the changes in the society of that time. Also is discussed about links between Russian and Baltic History in this time.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to give a systematic overview of the main facts and problems of Russian history in the 18th c. and to improve the basic course of Modern History.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The attested student  - will have the basic knowledge of terminology and research issues of the early modern history of Russia  - he/she will have primary information about political history and popular historic persons and elements of historical geography - the course aims to teach students to reflect critically on the characteristic features and epistemic objectives of the discipline of history
